Encode Sans Semi Condensed Thin Regular (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Thin', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Semi Condensed Thin Regular (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed Thin'.

Encode Sans Semi Condensed Light Regular (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed Light'.

Encode Sans Semi Condensed Regular (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed Medium'.

OK: Font has both Typographic Family Name (NID 16) and Typographic Subfamily Name (NID 17).

Critical

Encode Sans Semi Condensed SmBd Regular (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed SemiBold' ≠ 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed SmBd' (NID 1).

Pass

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Bold', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Semi Condensed Bold (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Bold', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Semi Condensed ExBd Regular (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

Encode Sans Semi Condensed Black Regular (EncodeSansSemiCondensed-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Condensed Black'.
